==演化==
据估计，大部分大型猫科动物的先祖于637万年前从[[猫亚科|猫亚科]]分裂出来<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/this-fossil-skull-unearthed-in-tibet-is-the-oldest-big-cat-ever-found-180947677/|title=This Fossil Skull Unearthed in Tibet Is the Oldest Big Cat Ever Found|date=2013-11-12|author=Joseph Stromberg|website=[[史密森尼学会|Smithsonian Institution]]|accessdate=2020-05-04|archive-date=2020-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522091700/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/this-fossil-skull-unearthed-in-tibet-is-the-oldest-big-cat-ever-found-180947677/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。另一方面，猫科主要由中小型动物组成，不仅包括[[家猫|家猫]]，还有[[美洲狮|美洲狮]]和[[猎豹|猎豹]]等体型较大的猫<ref name=MSW3>{{MSW3 Wozencraft|pages = 532–545|id=14000004}}</ref>。

2010年一项发表在《{{le|分子系统发育与进化期刊|Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution}}》的研究深入了解了大型猫科动物的确切进化关系<ref name=DavisLiMurphy2010>{{Cite journal |last=Davis |first=Brian W. |last2=Li |first2=Gang |last3=Murphy |first3=William J. |year=2010 |title=Supermatrix and species tree methods resolve phylogenetic relationships within the big cats, ''Panthera'' (Carnivora: Felidae) |journal=Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution |volume=56 |issue=1 |pages=64–76 |doi=10.1016/j.ympev.2010.01.036 |lastauthoramp=yes |pmid=20138224}}</ref>。研究表明，[[雪豹|雪豹]]和[[虎|虎]]是姊妹物种，[[狮|狮]]、[[豹|豹]]和[[美洲豹|美洲豹]]彼此间的联系更加紧密。虎和雪豹从先祖大猫分开约390万年。老虎之后在320万年前的[[上新世|上新世]]末期进化为独特物种。狮、豹和美洲虎的祖先与其他大型猫科动物相距430万到380万年。在360万到250万年间，美洲豹从先祖狮和豹中[[趨異演化|趨異演化]]。狮和豹大约于200万年前分裂<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/earth/hi/earth_news/newsid_8512000/8512455.stm | work=BBC News | title=Tiger's ancient ancestry revealed | date=2010-02-12 | accessdate=2010-04-26 | archive-date=2010-02-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100218032133/http://news.bbc.co.uk/earth/hi/earth_news/newsid_8512000/8512455.stm | dead-url=no }}</ref>。最早的大猫化石[[布氏豹|布氏豹]]可追溯到410万到595万年前，在西藏西南部发现<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Z. Jack Tseng |author2=Xiaoming Wang |author3=Graham J. Slater |author4=Gary T. Takeuchi |author5=Qiang Li |author6=Juan Liu |author7=Guangpu Xie |title=Himalayan fossils of the oldest known pantherine establish ancient origin of big cats |journal=Proceedings of the Royal Society B |date=2014-01-07 |volume=281 |number=1774 |page=20132686 |doi=10.1098/rspb.2013.2686 |pmid=24225466 |pmc=3843846}}</ref>。

